lead_paragraph: THE stock market has spent the better part of the last two weeks trying to figure out what higher bond yields really mean for equities. So far, it’s hard to conclude very much, except that higher yields have brought higher volatility to stocks, with the Dow Jones industrial average having either lost or gained more than 100 points in five of the last eight trading days.

headline.main: Mea Culpa, Said the Bond Market Watchers
